                   "message":  "audit(io-image): task #7 read-only preflight — halt-blocked-clean\n\nLands the audit content from ISSUE-98 (task #7). The dispatch\ncorrectly halted at one of its declared halt conditions\n(EXEC_STATUS: blocked, NEXT_ROLE: PLANNER_AI, EXIT_CODE: 0) but\nthe pre-fix queue runner mis-classified the non-zero loop exit as\na retryable failure. Queue runner fix landed separately at\n`136b800` and is documented as §14.10. This commit lands only the\naudit content (5 packet/log files); no source / test / Cargo\nchanges.\n\nAudit conclusion (full evidence in\n`ai_handoffs/ISSUE-98_EXEC_2026-05-22_23-26-07+0300.md`):\n- Q1: `crates/io-image/src/asset_store_stub.rs` is module-reachable\n  but consumer-unreachable. Zero in-tree code consumers of the stub\n  outside its own unit tests. `Cache` / `MemoryCache` are not\n  re-exported at the io-image crate root.\n- Q2: io-image\u0027s stub trait (`\u0026self`, infallible, counter-keyed\n  `Vec\u003cu8\u003e` AssetIds, `Send + Sync`) is shape-incompatible with\n  `rge_asset_store::Cache` (`\u0026mut self`, fallible, BLAKE3-keyed,\n  not `Send + Sync`, with `evict_lru` / `total_size` / `len`).\n- Q3: io-image has no content-addressed identity on `Image` — no\n  `content_hash()`, no canonical-bytes function, no `AssetId`\n  accessor, no `rge-asset-store` dependency.\n- Q4: zero present consumers. io-gltf consumes io-image\u0027s `Image`\n  data type but routes its caching through its own typed\n  `ImageAsset` adapter (#94 / `crates/io-gltf/src/asset_store_cache.rs`).\n- Q5: no bounded adapter dispatch justified by current code\n  evidence. Either path forward (stub deletion vs. designing a\n  content-addressed identity on `Image`) is human / Planner work,\n  not an autonomous bounded follow-up.\n\nThis is the second clean execution of a read-only audit shape\n(after #92 / task #4) — confirms the shape works correctly\nincluding its design-work-detection halts, when the queue runner\nrespects the EXEC_STATUS distinction.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
